        <item>
          <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
          <versionCode>00</versionCode>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>Natural Gas Pipeline Public Health Protection Act of 2017</b></p> <p>This bill suspends construction of natural gas facilities that have been issued a certificate of public convenience and necessity by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission until violations relating to air quality are remediated.</p> <p>It applies to a holder of a certificate that has not commenced construction of a facility for which such certificate was issued within the previous two years.</p>]]></text>
          <lastSummaryUpdateDate>2018-07-17T15:00:48Z</lastSummaryUpdateDate>
